					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>291 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>495</height>
										<width>340</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>350</height>
										<width>220</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>291 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and 3 at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each, marked by catchwords at the end.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="3" ruledLines="47" writtenLines="46">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible pricking and ruling in pencil, page by page. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of the folios indistinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written within ruling.</p>
									<p>Initial words in larger semi-cursive script. </p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation in a later hand in the upper left-hand corner of each recto.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the 14th century.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>An Italian note, signed by <name type="person" role="censor">Bart[olomeo] Rocca di Praterino</name>, giving permission to <name type="person" role="owner">Avraham Segre</name> to use the book according to his will: folio 291v.</p>
							<p>A legal document in Italian, on the quarto paper leaf attached on guard at the end of the voume, dated <date calendar="Hebrew">16 Marheshvan 5503</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">13 November 1742</date>). <name type="person" role="owner">Samson Segre</name> agrees to print the manuscript together with Jacob London and Isaac Berakhyah Kanton, in Amsterdam, London, or elsewhere.</p>
							<p>Inner side of folio 1r (front flyleaf): descriptions on modern paper of two works by <name type="person">Natanael Diodato Segre</name> (῾Atarat tiferet Savoya and Nezer ha-ḳodesh mi-Savoya). The Duke Charles Emmanuel is therein extolled. Dated <date calendar="Gregorian">1622</date>.</p>
						</additions>
